Colour . Dorsal surface of carapace yellowish orange to white, paler laterally and posteriorly; a broad whitish stripe proceeding backwards from the front; two large spots on the posterior part of the carapace, and two smaller ones on each lateral margin, the basal portion of the fingers, and a ring on each segment of the ambulatory legs, are all rust coloured (
Fig. 1
). Ventral surface paler grey.
